     <body>
     <div type="encomium">
   <l>REader, if thou fain wouldst know,</l>
   <l>To whose labours thou dost ow</l>
   <l>These sacred lines, think who't may be</l>
   <l>Seeks thy souls good, and that is he.</l>
   <l>Some say these writings <hi>Gerards</hi> be:</l>
   <l>He wrote indeed, but not to thee.</l>
   <l>He was to those that learned were,</l>
   <l>To thee he was not though be were.</l>
   <l>Before, thou couldst not understand,</l>
   <l>He's now translated to thy hand.</l>
   <l>Reade him, and use him as thy friend,</l>
   <l>And hee'l be thine unto the end.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>William Norrice.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
